{% comment %}
  subscription-widget.liquid
  Include this snippet in your product template: {% render 'subscription-widget', product: product %}

  This snippet:
  1. Creates the mount point div with all data attributes the widget JS needs
  2. Loads the widget script from your theme's assets
{% endcomment %}

{% assign subs_variant = product.selected_or_first_available_variant %}

<div
  id="subs-widget"
  data-shop-id="{{ shop.metafields.subscriptions.shop_id }}"
  data-app-url="{{ shop.metafields.subscriptions.app_url }}"
  data-portal-url="{{ shop.metafields.subscriptions.portal_url }}"
  data-variant-id="{{ subs_variant.id }}"
  data-price="{{ subs_variant.price | divided_by: 100.0 }}"
>
  {{- 'subscription-widget.js' | asset_url | script_tag -}}
</div>

{% comment %}
  SETUP INSTRUCTIONS:

  1. Upload subscription-widget.js to your theme's Assets folder

  2. Set the required metafields on your shop:
     - Namespace: subscriptions
     - Keys: shop_id, app_url, portal_url

     In Shopify Admin → Settings → Custom data → Shops → Add definition
     Or via the API:
       PATCH /admin/api/2024-01/shop.json
       {
         "shop": {
           "metafields": [
             { "namespace": "subscriptions", "key": "shop_id",    "value": "YOUR_DB_SHOP_ID",        "type": "single_line_text_field" },
             { "namespace": "subscriptions", "key": "app_url",    "value": "https://your-server.com", "type": "single_line_text_field" },
             { "namespace": "subscriptions", "key": "portal_url", "value": "https://your-portal.com", "type": "single_line_text_field" }
           ]
         }
       }

  3. Include the snippet in your product template:
     In product.liquid (or sections/main-product.liquid for Dawn theme),
     add this line after the buy button:

       {% render 'subscription-widget', product: product %}

  4. Test it:
     - Visit any product page on your store
     - You should see the "Purchase options" widget below the buy button
     - Selecting a plan and clicking "Subscribe now" should redirect to your portal
{% endcomment %}
